The paper deals with the trade-off between information locality and redundancy in codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also discusses the structure of linear codes meeting this trade-off, which involves combinatorial and algebraic techniques (cs.DS, cs.DC, cs.CC). Additionally, the paper may be relevant to the sub-category of coding theory (cs.SI).
